        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-12-08T07:09:12.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Had a 1994 Jean-Marc Morey Caillerets last night that also truly transcended the vintage\u2019s reputation - just a great Caillerets.</p>\n<p>And I\u2019m glad the Verget showed so well. Your analogy makes sense, too. In their marriage of amplitude and incisiveness, Jean-Marie\u2019s wines remind me most of Ramonet among today\u2019s white Burgundy producers.</p>",
